<div id="review_582683665" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/582683665" />
    <a title="Diana Febry" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7935647-diana-febry"><img alt="Diana Febry" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442628269p2/7935647.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/582683665?book_show_action=true">Apr 06, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Diana Febry" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Diana Febry" href="/user/show/7935647-diana-febry">Diana Febry</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer582683665" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12233869948332377743">I recommend this book for readers searching for a good story and a fast paced read. <br/>Its a vampire story so stating the obvious there is some gore, immortality, fangs and stakes but within the standard elements is weaved an intriguing story covering the 1940s to present day. The story covers the themes of good versus evil, the obsessive need for revenge, love and what is means to be &quot;human.&quot; It also touches on issues of abusive relationships and drug addiction. <br/>The story cracks on at a good pace </span>
  <span id="freeText12233869948332377743" style="display:none">I recommend this book for readers searching for a good story and a fast paced read. <br />Its a vampire story so stating the obvious there is some gore, immortality, fangs and stakes but within the standard elements is weaved an intriguing story covering the 1940s to present day. The story covers the themes of good versus evil, the obsessive need for revenge, love and what is means to be "human." It also touches on issues of abusive relationships and drug addiction. <br />The story cracks on at a good pace with the action taking place through the decades and moving across continents. With high readability and plenty of twists and turns I found this an enjoyable read. <br />My personal preference would have been to have fewer "events" but more depth to the characters. That being said the writing style allows for a lot of ground to be covered and there was never a dull moment. <br />An enjoyable fast paced story. </span>
  <a data-text-id="12233869948332377743" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


